The Caretaker and Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has constituted committees for the party’s national convention in March. The heads of the various committees include the Deputy President of the Senate, Senator Ovie Omo-Agege; Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami; Governor Ben Ayade of Cross River State, Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State, Governor Dave Umahi of Ebonyi State, Minister of Foreign Affairs, Geoffrey Onyema, etc.
The mandate of the APC National Convention Sub-Committees includes coordinating activities within the respective committees to ensure a hitch free National Convention for the All Progressives Congress at the Eagle Square in Abuja.
